supportDesc.extent: 106. Fols 98, 101r and 104-105 are blank, fol. 107 was originally also blank. 112 85 .

foliation.p: Foliated in the top right corner. The number 30 was skipped.

condition.p: On fol. 107 there are two holes. The second and the third gathering were mixed up when the manuscript was rebound.

layout.p: Written in one column with 22 to 25 (fols 1-94) lines per page. Decorated, coloured and gilded initials, usually at the beginning of a new item. Red or blue initials and majuscles, red rubrics and running titles.

decoNote.p:
There are several decorated, coloured and gilded initials, usually at the beginning of a new item:
fol. 1r: initial M (10 lines) with foliage and floral decoDesc to the bottom margin.
fol. 4v: inital B (9 lines) with foliage and floral decoDesc to the bottom and left margin.
fol. 25r: inital S (2 lines) with foliage and floral decoDesc to the left margin.
fol. 27v: initial S (7 lines) with foliage and floral decoDesc to the left and bottom margin.
fol. 37v: initial H (5 lines) with foliage decoDesc to the left and bottom margin.
fol. 40r: initial N (4 lines) with foliage decoation to the left margin.
fol. 51r: initial B (3 lines) with foliage decoDesc to the left margin.
fol. 53r: initial O (4 lines) with foliagedecoation to the left margin.
fol. 63r: initial T (5 lines) with foliage and floral decoDesc to the left, bottom and right margin.
fol. 85r: initial K (5 lines) with foliage decoDesc to the left, bottom and right margin.
fol. 88r: inital E (3 lines) with foliage and floral decoDesc to the left, top and right margin.
fol. 90r: inital H (4 lines) with foliage and floral decoDesc to all margins.

additions.p:
There are several notes on fol 107r. On fol. 107v is written: Hafniæ,
Anno 1685 Den 20 August
kiőbte Jeg; Strange Fy
ren; denne Bog paa en
Auction. A prayer seems to have been erased above the sentence.
Two slips of paper with information about the gatherings are inserted at the back of the codex.

origin.p: The manuscript was written in Denmark at the end of the fifteenth century.
